Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp} for the rice.

When boiling, add the @Basmati rice{150%g} and cook for ~{12%minutes}.

Drain in a #sieve{}, pop back in the saucepan, cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

When the oil is hot, add the @British pork mince{240%g} and cook until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}. Use a #wooden spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Drain and discard any excess fat from the mince, then season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Stir the garlic and @Central American style spice mix{1%pack} (add less if you don't like heat) into the pork. Stir-fry until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add the @tomato passata{1%jar}, @water{150%ml} for the sauce, @chicken stock paste{10%g} and a pinch of @?sugar{pinch} (if you have any).

Stir together and bring to the boil, then reduce the heat. Simmer until the sauce has thickened, ~{10-12%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} then remove from the heat.

Meanwhile, halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}. Pop them into a #bowl{} with the @olive oil{1%tbsp}.

Roughly chop the @chives{1%bunch}, then add half to the bowl with the tomatoes.

Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, mix and set aside.

Thinly slice the @red chilli{1/2}.

Grate the @mature Cheddar cheese{30%g}.

Have a quick tidy up while everything cooks.

When everything is ready, divide the rice between your serving bowls and top with the pork chilli.

Spoon over the tomato salsa and scatter with cheese over one-third of the burrito bowl. Finish with a dollop of @creme fraiche{75%g}.

Garnish with the remaining chives and the chilli (for any adults who would like a little more heat). Enjoy!